rows.name: Kim Schwenk
rows.title: Vice President of Nursing and Chief Nursing Officer
rows.details: High influence within the organization, director-level with operational decision-making authority. Responsible for over 1,000 nursing staff and led Magnet re-designation work. Her sepsis priorities include triage/nursing sepsis screening, nursing training and compliance on early identification/bundle delivery, and staffing/retention impacts on response times. She controls nursing protocols, screening workflows, and bedside bundle execution. She is a primary champion for IntelliSep adoption discussions. Conversation starters should focus on balancing faster sepsis detection with nursing workload and how a low-workflow diagnostic fits into staffing and competency plans.
